&lt;p&gt;Well, it&apos;s definitely a little more involved than that.   &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;    That leaves the destination for that address with a listener attached so it thinks it&apos;s activated.   I&apos;m tracing it through now.   Thus, the second call just re-uses it and doesn&apos;t fail. &lt;/p&gt;

